text: Catherine of France may refer to: * Catherine of France, Countess of Montpensier (1378-1388), daughter of Charles V of France * Catherine of Valois (1401-1437), daughter of Charles VI of France, queen consort of Henry V of England * Catherine of France, Countess of Charolais (1428-1446), daughter of Charles VII of France, first spouse to Charles I, Duke of Burgundy == See also == * Catherine of Valois (disambiguation)
title: Catherine of France
